docs.lead_paragraph: MUSIC by South American composers has been heard in Paris during the past season with renewed interest. Works by many composers from the Southern republics include those by Carlos Pedrell, Jose Andre, Alberto Williams and Humberto Allende, whose "Trois Tonadas," based on popular country tunes of Chile, was given under the baton of Walther Straram.
